{"types":[{"section":"\n{{fr-noun|m}}\n\n# [[pride]]; [[pridefulness]]; [[haughtiness]], [[arrogance]]\n#: {{ux|fr|Le revers a blessé son '''orgueil.'''|The misfortune hurt his '''pride.'''}}\n#: {{ux|fr|Je ne prendrai pas de charité; j'ai mon '''orgueil'''.|I won't take any charity; I still have my '''pride.'''}}\n#* {{RQ:Saint-Exupéry Petit Prince|chapter=VII|page=30|passage=Et toute la journée il répète comme toi&nbsp;: «&thinsp;Je suis un homme sérieux&nbsp;! Je suis un homme sérieux&nbsp;!&thinsp;» et ça le fait gonfler d''''orgueil'''.|translation=And all day he says over and over, just like you: ‘I am busy with matters of consequence!’ And that makes him swell up with '''pride'''.}}\n\n====Usage notes====\nUnlike cognate terms in other languages (e.g. {{m+|es|orgullo}}, {{m+|ca|orgull}}, {{m+|it|orgoglio}}), {{m|fr||orgueil}} chiefly carries the negative connotations of {{m|en|pride}}. The positive senses (related to self-esteem) are expressed by {{m|fr|fierté}}.\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|fr|enorgueillir}}\n* {{l|fr|orgueilleux}}\n\n","alt":[],"syn":[],"type":"noun","forms":[{"g":"m","n":"s"}],"html":"<p><span class=\"headword-line\"><strong class=\"Latn headword\" lang=\"fr\">orgueil</strong>&nbsp;<span class=\"gender\"><abbr title=\"masculine gender\">m</abbr></span> (<i>plural</i> <b class=\"Latn form-of lang-fr p-form-of\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/orgueils#French\" title=\"orgueils\">orgueils</a></b>)</span>\n</p><ol><li><a href=\"/wiki/pride\" title=\"pride\">pride</a>; <a href=\"/wiki/pridefulness\" title=\"pridefulness\">pridefulness</a>; <a href=\"/wiki/haughtiness\" title=\"haughtiness\">haughtiness</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/arrogance\" title=\"arrogance\">arrogance</a>\n<dl><dd><div class=\"h-usage-example\"><i class=\"Latn mention e-example\" lang=\"fr\">Le revers a blessé son <b>orgueil.</b></i><dl><dd><span class=\"e-translation\">The misfortune hurt his <b>pride.</b></span></dd></dl></div></dd>\n<dd><div class=\"h-usage-example\"><i class=\"Latn mention e-example\" lang=\"fr\">Je ne prendrai pas de charité; j'ai mon <b>orgueil</b>.</i><dl><dd><span class=\"e-translation\">I won't take any charity; I still have my <b>pride.</b></span></dd></dl></div></dd></dl>\n<ul><li><div class=\"citation-whole\"><span class=\"cited-source\"><span class=\"None\" lang=\"und\"><b>1943</b></span>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antoine_Saint-Exup%C3%A9ry\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Antoine Saint-Exupéry\">Antoine Saint-Exupéry</a>, chapter VII, in <cite>Le petit prince</cite> [<cite><span class=\"e-translation\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Little_Prince\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:The Little Prince\">The Little Prince</a></span></cite>], New York: <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reynal_%26_Hitchcock\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Reynal &amp; Hitchcock\">Reynal &amp; Hitchcock</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://archive.org/details/le-petit-prince-antoine-st-ex-livre/page/n29/mode/1up\">page <span class=\"None\" lang=\"und\">30</span></a>:</span><dl><dd><div class=\"h-quotation\"><span class=\"Latn e-quotation cited-passage\" lang=\"fr\">Et toute la journée il répète comme toi&nbsp;: « Je suis un homme sérieux&nbsp;! Je suis un homme sérieux&nbsp;! » et ça le fait gonfler d'<b>orgueil</b>.</span><dl><dd><span class=\"e-translation\">And all day he says over and over, just like you: ‘I am busy with matters of consequence!’ And that makes him swell up with <b>pride</b>.</span></dd></dl></div></dd></dl></div></li></ul></li></ol><div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading4\"><h4 id=\"Usage_notes\">Usage notes</h4><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=orgueil&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10\" title=\"Edit section: Usage notes\"><span>edit</span></a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></div><p>Unlike cognate terms in other languages (e.g. Spanish <i class=\"Latn mention\" lang=\"es\"><a href=\"/wiki/orgullo#Spanish\" title=\"orgullo\">orgullo</a></i>, Catalan <i class=\"Latn mention\" lang=\"ca\"><a href=\"/wiki/orgull#Catalan\" title=\"orgull\">orgull</a></i>, Italian <i class=\"Latn mention\" lang=\"it\"><a href=\"/wiki/orgoglio#Italian\" title=\"orgoglio\">orgoglio</a></i>), <i class=\"Latn mention\" lang=\"fr\">orgueil</i> chiefly carries the negative connotations of <i class=\"Latn mention\" lang=\"en\"><a href=\"/wiki/pride#English\" title=\"pride\">pride</a></i>. The positive senses (related to self-esteem) are expressed by <i class=\"Latn mention\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/fiert%C3%A9#French\" title=\"fierté\">fierté</a></i>.\n</p><div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading4\"><h4 id=\"Derived_terms\">Derived terms</h4><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=orgueil&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11\" title=\"Edit section: Derived terms\"><span>edit</span></a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></div><ul><li><span class=\"Latn\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/enorgueillir#French\" title=\"enorgueillir\">enorgueillir</a></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"Latn\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/orgueilleux#French\" title=\"orgueilleux\">orgueilleux</a></span></li></ul>","trans":["pride","pridefulness","haughtiness, arrogance","pride","pridefulness","haughtiness, arrogance","pride","pridefulness","haughtiness, arrogance"]}],"title":"orgueil","id":"1300308","audios":[{"name":"Fr-orgueil.ogg","url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/49/Fr-orgueil.ogg"}],"ipas":["/ɔʁ.ɡœj/"],"pronunSection":"\n* {{fr-IPA}}\n* {{audio|fr|Fr-orgueil.ogg|text=l'orgueil}}\n\n","pronunHtml":"<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Wiktionary:International_Phonetic_Alphabet\" title=\"Wiktionary:International Phonetic Alphabet\">IPA</a><sup>(<a href=\"/wiki/Appendix:French_pronunciation\" title=\"Appendix:French pronunciation\">key</a>)</sup>: <span class=\"IPA\">/ɔʁ.ɡœj/</span></li>\n<li><style data-mw-deduplicate